text.tspan: The past seven years have been the hottest ever recorded.
The need for indoor cooling is strongly on the rise. Whether
we are shopping in a mall, working in an office, or staying in
a hospital, a temperature-controlled atmosphere is
pleasant, necessary, and can even be crucial to our health.
Intelligent air conditioning systems not only do their job as
usual, they do it the smart way. Thanks to targeted cooling
they help reduce power consumption and increase comfort.
To adjust performance to real needs, these devices are able
to 'see', 'hear' and 'feel' their surroundings – with the help
of sensors and controllers. This “intelligence” can save a lot
